  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Server Entrypoint**\n\nOkay, I\'m now crafting the `server.ts` entry point. The plan is to handle serving static assets, using Vite middleware during development and the `dist/` folder in production. I\'m also integrating the Gemini API client. I\'m focusing on the \"AI Jeweler Stylist\" chat functionality. I am now exploring the Gemini API client.\n\n\n**Refining API Initialization**\n\nI\'ve just pinpointed a critical issue regarding the Gemini API key. Apparently, the application will crash if the key is missing during initialization. To sidestep this, I\'m refactoring the `GoogleGenAI` client initialization, moving it into the route handler. This lazy initialization will allow me to check for the key\'s presence, handle the absence gracefully, and prevent crashes.\n\n\n**Crafting `server.ts` Logic**\n\nI\'m now fully immersed in the `server.ts` file. I\'m building out the `/api/stylist/chat` route, focusing on delivering JSON responses, ensuring CORS handling, JSON body parsing, and robust error management. I\'ve also confirmed the Vite middleware integration and finalized the necessary imports for `express`, `path`, and `dotenv`, including running `dotenv.config()` for key management. The goal is a resilient and well-structured server entry point.\n\n\n**Structuring Server Environment**\n\nI\'m now focusing on setting up the environment variables and the initial structure for `server.ts`. I have confirmed that I can load environment variables from the `.env` file, and I\'m currently reviewing imports and the essential structural components, as well as the lazy-initialized Gemini AI client. I am implementing a robust `getGeminiClient()` function to handle API key presence and prevent crashes, as well as the required imports.\n\n\n**Embracing Poetic Jewelry Style**\n\nI\'ve refined the stylistic approach, aiming for an elegant, poetic voice inspired by luxury French jewelry houses. I now focus on beautiful Spanish descriptions, incorporating \"tallado,\" \"brillante,\" and \"atemporal.\" My focus is to evoke a sense of high craftsmanship. I\'ll evaluate designs through the lens of metal-gemstone harmony, crafting poetic stories about gemstone significance, and providing stylish suggestions for wearing each piece.\n\n\n**Implementing API Fallback**\n\nI\'m now implementing the fallback response for the `/api/stylist/chat` endpoint. I\'ve designed a poetic response to use if the Gemini API key is missing. This elegant fallback, offering stylized descriptions of jewelry pieces, ensures the app functions beautifully, even without external API access, while also subtly prompting the user to provide the key. I\'m focusing on crafting a very evocative response that can be used for initial interaction.\n\n\n**Refining Response Construction**\n\nI\'m now integrating the design context into the Gemini API call. I\'m focusing on ensuring proper formatting of the message and current design details. I\'m using the `currentDesign` object for context and constructing the prompt dynamically. I am preparing the `contents` array with the user message and design context. I\'m prepending design details to the prompt, to give the model the precise details of the item the user is trying to design. I am also planning on including history to improve results.\n\n\n**Finalizing Elegant Responses**\n\nI\'m now integrating stylistic refinements into the responses, aiming for a poetic, sophisticated, and exclusive tone mirroring high-end Parisian jewelry houses like Cartier. I\'m incorporating eloquent Spanish with terms like \'orfebrer\303\255a\' and \'destello celestial\'. I aim to offer mystical stories about gemstones, suggest exclusive aesthetic combinations, and validate the client\'s exquisite taste. I\'m ensuring responses remain elegant and captivating.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the backend entry point `server.ts`. This file implements the lazy initialization pattern for our Gemini API key and sets up the Express server with Vite middleware in development or static asset serving in production. If the user hasn\'t configured a Gemini key yet, the API gracefully falls back to an elegant, poeteic luxury jeweler response, ensuring the app remains fully functional and never crashes on load."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 12
      nanos: 752027344
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
