    thinking: "**Constructing Customizer Architecture**\n\nI\'ve successfully established the basic types and static data. My immediate focus is now on constructing modular subcomponents to enhance `/src/App.tsx`. The goal is to build `/src/components/AtelierCustomizer.tsx`, an interactive Atelier builder for users. This will handle the app\'s core functionality, enabling a robust and flexible architecture.\n\n\n**Designing Interactive Visualization**\n\nI\'m now fully immersed in developing the interactive visualization within `/src/components/AtelierCustomizer.tsx`. It will display dynamic SVG renders that respond in real time to user selections. I\'ve decided to include item types, and gemstones to enable a gorgeous animated SVG with neon gradients. I want to emulate high-end luxury jeweler software. Dropdown controls will be used to select metal, jewelry type, gem, cut, carats, engraving.\n\n\n**Defining Component Interaction**\n\nI\'m currently focused on defining the specific component interactions within `/src/components/AtelierCustomizer.tsx`. I\'m going to start with a grid selection for metals, gemstones, segmented buttons for gemstone cuts, a carat slider, and a custom engraving input. I\'m imagining an \"AI Stylist Analysis\" button, integrating Aurelia\'s feedback seamlessly. The ultimate goal is to build the custom ring visualizer.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will now create the interactive design customizer component `/src/components/AtelierCustomizer.tsx`. This customizer allows users to select jewelry types, noble metals, gemstone types, cuts, carats, and custom inscriptions. It features an interactive, highly-stylized SVG render engine that adapts colors, gem scales, and labels in real time, with smooth CSS animations and an elegant luxury interface. It also includes an \"Ask AI Stylist\" integration that feeds the active configuration directly to the AI chat."
