  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Aporro\'s Niche**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on Aporro Jewelry\'s core identity. My focus is the **Iced Out / Streetwear / Hip Hop / Urban Luxury** style. I see key product offerings as Cuban Link Chains, Tennis Bracelets, Iced-out Pendants (including custom photo, letter, Angel, Jesus Pieces, Animal pendants), Rings, and Grillz. I\'m noting the prominence of Gold and White Gold (silver color) materials.\n\n\n**Refining Design Aesthetics**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on Aporro\'s core identity. My focus is the **Iced Out / Streetwear / Hip Hop / Urban Luxury** style. I see key product offerings as Cuban Link Chains, Tennis Bracelets, Iced-out Pendants (including custom photo, letter, Angel, Jesus Pieces, Animal pendants), Rings, and Grillz. I\'m noting the prominence of Gold and White Gold (silver color) materials.\n\nI\'m now thinking about material considerations: I\'ll include Rose Gold and Platinum. I\'m focusing on \"shiny gems\" like Moissanite and VVS Cubic Zirconia (or Diamonds/Gemstones like Black Diamonds, Sapphires, Rubies, Emeralds) for that signature \"iced-out\" look. I\'m making sure I use key hip-hop terminology such as \"Iced Out\", \"Cuban Link\", \"Micro Pave\", \"Prong Set\", \"Choker\", \"Drip\", \"Moissanite\", \"Solitario\", \"Grillz\", and \"Bling Bling\". I need to redesign **AYA GOLDEN** to have that Aporro-style urban streetwear luxury / hip hop \"iced out\" vibe, retaining the interactive features.\n\n\n**Visualizing The Aesthetic**\n\nI\'m now picturing the Aporro website. I\'m imagining golden or diamond sparkles as the background particles. The logo will be a glowing diamond-and-gold AYA monogram on black satin fabric. I want the homepage and product pages to be an elevated version of the existing site, drawing inspiration from Aporro.eu\'s sleek design. I\'m focusing on modifying existing components to reflect the hip-hop aesthetic.\n\n\n**Designing Customizer Features**\n\nI\'m now outlining key product customizations. I\'ll offer a Pharaoh Iced-Out Ring, Diamond Grillz sets, and Custom Photo Necklaces. I will use the \"Iced-Out Lab\" to let customers configure various elements for a custom piece: like a Miami Cuban Link, a Tennis Chain, or a Luxury Grillz. I need to make the customizer let the user select metal, stone type, and style, with interactive visual renderings. I need to add that same customizer functionality to the styling assistant.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 8
      nanos: 412538130
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
